e%20straits.%20If%20the%20warship%20is%20returning%20to%20its%20base%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20the%20passage%20is%20not%20closed%2C%26quot%3B%20Turkey's%20foreign%20minister%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalnews.com%2Fnaval-news%2F2022%2F02%2Fturkey-closes-the-dardanelles-and-bosphorus-to-warships%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BAll%20governments%2C%20riparian%20and%20non-riparian%2C%20were%20warned%20not%20to%20send%20warships%20across%20the%20straits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnkara's%20invocation%20of%20the%20convention%20is%20seen%20as%20significant%20because%20it%20has%20prevented%20Russia%20from%20bolstering%20its%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet.%20If%20Turkey%20were%20to%20open%20the%20straits%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20thing%20you%20would%20see%20is%20a%20significant%20naval%20reinforcement%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20Russian%20fleet%2C%20and%20that%20isn't%20in%20Ukraine's%20interest%20or%20ours%2C%26quot%3B%20Ben%20Wallace%2C%20Britain's%20defense%20minister%20at%20the%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fglobalassets%2Fmedia-library---content--migration%2Ffiles%2Fshangri-la-dialogue%2F2023%2Ffinal-transcripts%2Fp-2%2Fsecond-plenary-session---qa---as-delivered.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Shangri-La%20Dialogue%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Smoke%20fire%20oil%20fuel%20tank%20drone%20attack%20Sevastopol%20Crimea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6463ee7d7224930019f326bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221181%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESmoke%20rising%20from%20a%20fuel%20tank%20after%20an%20attack%20in%20Sevastopol%20in%20April.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FStringer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Turkey's%20move%20has%20limited%20Russian%20naval%20movements%2C%20experts%20differ%20on%20its%20overall%20impact%20on%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInitially%2C%20it%20was%20thought%20that%20it%20was%20a%20big%20deal%20that%20some%20of%20the%20Russian%20warships%20were%20prevented%20from%20entering%20the%20Black%20Sea.%20But%20Russia%20had%20a%20massive%20naval%20presence%20there%20anyway%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20six%20ships%20from%20its%20Baltic%20and%20Northern%20fleets%20that%20entered%20the%20sea%20before%20Turkey%20invoked%20the%20convention%2C%20Volodymyr%20Dubovyk%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Odessa's%20I.%20Mechnikov%20National%20University%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDubovyk%20added%20that%20Russia's%20ships%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20didn't%20give%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bdecisive%20edge%20over%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20because%20of%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20Ukraine's%20attacks%2C%20those%20ships%20had%20become%20%26quot%3Bsitting%20ducks%26quot%3B%20that%20had%20%26quot%3Bto%20hide%20away%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20coast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20warships%20still%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FThe_Lookout_N%2Fstatus%2F1710616079020482891%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappear%20to%20be%20stationed%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Sevastopol%2C%20the%20main%20Russian%20naval%20base%20in%20Crimea%2C%20but%20Ukraine's%20success%20in%20targeting%20that%20base%20and%20Russian%20forces%20nearby%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-flagship-moskva-sinking-marks-new-era-of-naval-warfare-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20probably%20have%20a%20lasting%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20these%20developments%20are%20going%20to%20contribute%20to%20a%20change%20in%20thinking%20about%20the%20role%20of%20naval%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20Dubovyk%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAllied%20help%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Turkey%20NATO%20Romania%20navy%20Black%20Sea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dd4d158fd9db254a82d0274%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22934%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Turkish%20navy%20frigate%20alongside%20a%20Romanian%20frigate%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20in%20February%202018.%3Cp%3ENATO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIulia-Sabina%20Joja%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea%20program%20at%20the%20Middle%20East%20Institute%2C%20a%20think%20tank%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20said%20the%20convention%20also%20allowed%20Turkey%20to%20shape%20the%20international%20response%20to%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Montreux%20Convention%20is%20confusing%2C%26quot%3B%20Joja%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20actually%20states%20that%20when%20Turkey%20is%20not%20a%20belligerent%20but%20feels%20threatened%2C%20then%20it%20can%20act%20as%20if%20it%20were%20a%20belligerent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20case%2C%20as%20Joja%20noted%2C%20the%20decision%20about%20which%20warships%20can%20enter%20the%20Black%20Sea%20is%20entirely%20up%20to%20the%20Turkish%20government%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20200319171226%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fsam.baskent.edu.tr%2Fbelge%2FMontreux_ENG.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20convention%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(Merchant%20ships%20can%20pass%20through%20the%20straits%20freely%2C%20even%20during%20wartime%2C%20and%20satellite%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fwolf-ships-clothing-russias-militarization-civilian-vessels-black-sea%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimagery%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20Russia%20is%20using%20them%20to%20move%20military%20hardware%20through%20the%20sea.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20provision%20could%20allow%20Turkey%20to%20let%20warships%20from%20NATO%20navies%20into%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20and%20some%20experts%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2F2023%2F07%2F25%2Fnato-convoys-can-protect-ukraine-s-grain-harvest-from-putin%2F541a151e-2aa3-11ee-a948-a5b8a9b62d84_story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvocated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20alliance%20seek%20access%20to%20the%20sea%20to%20escort%20merchant%20vessels%20carrying%20Ukrainian%20grain%2C%20thus%20helping%20circumvent%20Russia's%20blockade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221492%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20Izmail%20Danube%20river%20grain%20cargo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65304d98211def8ed838b5c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221119%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20cargo%20ship%20passes%20a%20beach%20on%20the%20Danube%20River%2C%20which%20is%20being%20used%20for%20Ukrainian%20grain%20shipments%2C%20in%20Izmail%20in%20August.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20convention%20may%20allow%20such%20an%20action%2C%20going%20through%20with%20it%20would%20be%20politically%20difficult%20for%20NATO%20and%20for%20Ankara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20two%20unknowns%20here%3A%20whether%20the%20Turkish%20government%20is%20willing%20to%20let%20NATO%20maritime%20defense%20capabilities%20in%20and%20whether%20NATO%20allies%20have%20the%20political%20will%20to%20build%20a%20credible%20deterrence%20and%20defense%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20region%2C%26quot%3B%20Joja%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurkey%20is%20a%20NATO%20member%20but%20maintains%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20Russia.%20That%20has%2C%20at%20times%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturkey-russia-s400-too-politically-costly-to-get-rid-of-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrustrated%20other%20NATO%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Ankara%20used%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href