early%20five%20months%20after%20the%20top%20court%20heard%20arduous%20arguments%20for%20and%20against%20the%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20matter%20garnered%20a%20lot%20of%20anticipation%20and%20thousands%20of%20listeners%20tuned%20in%20when%20the%20CJI%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20degree%20of%20agreement%20and%20degree%20of%20disagreement%20%5Bamong%20the%20judges%5D.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENot%20long%20after%2C%20he%20spoke%20of%20the%20doctrine%20of%20separation%20of%20powers.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20doctrine%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%20means%20that%20each%20of%20the%20three%20organs%20of%20the%20State%20performs%20distinct%20functions.%20No%20branch%20can%20function%20like%20any%20other%E2%80%99s%20function.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20compel%20Parliament%20or%20state%20assemblies%20to%20create%20a%20new%20institution%20of%20marriage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpdf.sciencedirectassets.com%2F271658%2F1-s2.0-S0144818800X00543%2F1-s2.0-014481889290040X%2Fmain.pdf%5C%22%3EA%20principal-agent%20relationship%20is%20often%20used%20to%20describe%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20interaction%20between%20lawmakers%20and%20the%20executive%20tasked%20with%20carrying%20out%20the%20legislators%E2%80%99%20wishes.%20The%20main%20objective%20here%20is%20to%20establish%20the%20circumstances%20that%20will%20give%20the%20principal%20confidence%20that%20its%20wishes%20are%20being%20carried%20out%20by%20its%20agents%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20their%20component%20parts%20may%20differ%20significantly%20from%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F26363248%3FtypeAccessWorkflow%3Dlogin%5C%22%3EArie%20Rosen%2C%20in%20his%20article%20%E2%80%98Statutory%20Interpretation%20and%20the%20Many%20Virtues%20of%20Legislation%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20condenses%20the%20questions%20of%20interpretive%20values%20to%20%E2%80%9Cceteris%20paribus%2C%20how%20the%20deference%20and%20respect%20we%20owe%20to%20legislative%20decisions%20should%20affect%20the%20way%20we%20interpret%20them%E2%80%9D.%20To%20this%20contention%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20question%20of%20which%20approach%20is%20appropriate%20depends%20on%20the%20ultimate%20value%20and%20purpose%20we%20attribute%20to%20the%20legislative%20process.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EQueer%20rights%20and%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Fsamesex-marriage-verdict-live-updates-supreme-court-verdict-lgbtqia-special-marriage-act-cji-chandrachud-11697505822651.html%5C%22%3EJustice%20S.%20Ravindra%20Bhat%20noted%20in%20his%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20marriage%20equality%2C%20%E2%80%9CRight%20to%20cohabiting%20cannot%20lead%20to%20setting%20up%20of%20an%20institution%E2%80%A6%20ordering%20a%20social%20institution%20or%20rearranging%20existing%20social%20structures%20would%20require%20construction%20of%20new%20code%20and%20also%20require%20marriage%20laws%20concerning%20alimony%20etc%E2%80%A6%20queer%20people%20have%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20dignity%20and%20to%20choose%20a%20partner.%20We%20disagree%20with%20the%20CJI%20in%20this%20regard%20which%20forms%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20final%20conclusions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20an%20important%20observation%20by%20Justice%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20view%20that%20needs%20further%20reflection.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%20view%20of%20love%20that%20places%20a%20premium%20on%20intimacy%20within%20the%20boundaries%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20privacy%20calls%20for%20non-interference%20since%2C%20in%20its%20traditional%20liberal%20form%2C%20privacy%20refers%20to%20the%20right%20to%20be%20free%20from%20outside%20interference.%20This%20idea%20has%20been%20used%20to%20argue%20against%20recognising%20the%20relationships%20that%20result%20from%20love%20and%20does%20not%20necessarily%20require%20doing%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccordingly%2C%20if%20we%20view%20the%20right%20to%20love%20as%20a%20crucial%20component%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20quest%20for%20self-fulfilment%20and%20self-respect%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnujslawreview.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F12-3-4-Chaudhary.pdf%5C%22%3Efailing%20to%20give%20full%20acknowledgement%20to%20any%20expression%20of%20that%20love%20would%20be%20a%20violation%20of%20that%20right%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fyogyakartaprinciples.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F11%2FA5_yogyakartaWEB-2.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Yogyakarta%20Principles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20were%20widely%20cited%20to%20define%20the%20rights%20of%20transgender%20people%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ENALSA%3C%2Fem%3E%20verdict%20(2014)%20in%20the%20framework%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20legal%20system%2C%20strangely%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20disregarded%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%20judgment.%20Particularly%2C%20Principle%2024%2C%20which%20addresses%20the%20right%20to%20have%20a%20family%2C%20unambiguously%20ensures%20that%20members%20of%20the%20queer%20community%20can%20get%20married%2C%20have%20children%2C%20and%20choose%20surrogacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhen%20the%20fundamental%20guidance%20offered%20by%20globally%20renowned%20organisations%20like%20the%20International%20Commission%20of%20Jurists%20and%20the%20International%20Service%20for%20Human%20Rights%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20disregarded%20in%20the%20process%2C%20the%20discrepancy%20between%20legal%20interpretations%20is%20especially%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20numerous%20legal%20judgments%20have%20consistently%20read%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20in%20a%20way%20that%20recognises%20the%20contextual%20foundations%20of%20core%20Yogyakarta%20Principles.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20high%20court%20wisely%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20right%20to%20marry%20a%20person%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20choice%20is%20integral%20to%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D%20in%20its%20deliberations%20on%20the%20matter%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F78371545%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESweta%20Dogra%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-649083%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court.%20In%20the%20background%20is%20a%20pride%20flag.%20Photos%3A%20File%20and%20Flickr%2FQuinn%20Dombrowski%20(CC%20BY-SA%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStructures%20and%20compositions%20of%20judicial%20machinery%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EActivists%20and%20members%20of%20the%20community%20criticised%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20Transgender%20Persons%20Right%20to%20Protection%20Bill%20for%20several%20reasons%2C%20including%20the%20way%20it%20characterised%20transgender%20people%20as%20%E2%80%9Cneither%20wholly%20female%20nor%20wholly%20male.%E2%80%9D%20The%20measure%20was%20then%20referred%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee.%20The%20Bill%20was%20brought%20back%20by%20the%20government%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20December%202018%2C%20where%20it%20was%20approved%20with%2027%20modifications%20that%20changed%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20transgender%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20recognise%20the%20right%20to%20gender%20identity%20is%20one%20of%20the%20primary%20criticisms%20levelled%20against%20it.%20The%20Bill%20only%20permits%20a%20person%20to%20be%20labelled%20as%20%E2%80%9Ctransgender%E2%80%9D%20on%20their%20certificate%20up%20until%20the%20point%20at%20which%20they%20have%20sex%20reassignment%20surgery%20and%20apply%20for%20a%20new%20certificate.%20A%20clause%20to%20establish%20a%20district%20screening%20committee%20was%20also%20inserted.%20Based%20on%20its%20recommendations%2C%20the%20district%20magistrate%20will%20issue%20a%20gender%20identity%20certificate.%20Activists%20protested%20this%20move%20by%20asking%20%E2%80%9CHow%20will%20district%20magistrates%20understand%20what%20the%20transgender%20community%20goes%20through%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%2Fabout%2FThe_Future_of_Human_Rights.html%3Fid%3DNjaIQgAACAAJ%26redir_esc%3Dy%5C%22%3EPost-colonial%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkalpanakannabiran.com%2Fbooks%2F%5C%22%3Escholars%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20emphasised%20that%20focusing%20solely%20on%20legal%20rights%20without%20challenging%20systems%20like%20colonialism%2C%20neoliberalism%2C%20authoritarianism%2C%20patriarchy%2C%20and%20class%20that%20restrict%20access%20to%20legal%20rights%20reduces%20human%20rights%20to%20merely%20legal%20changes%20that%20only%20have%20a%20very%20limited%20impact%20on%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fhl%3Den%26lr%3D%26id%3DAGGRBgAAQBAJ%26oi%3Dfnd%26pg%3DPT5%26ots%3DoFp86fdDHl%26sig%3Doa1TSUPAUfLL5VhuwBfdabI3u8U%26redir_esc%3Dy%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3ESouth%20Asian%20scholars%20have%20also%20underlined%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20need%20to%20understand%20how%20social%20battles%20for%20securing%20and%20exercising%20legal%20rights%20are%20affected%20by%20factors%20such%20as%20power%2C%20unequal%20access%20to%20resources%2C%20and%20political%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20legal%20battle%20for%20marriage%20equality%20has%20experienced%20the%20same%20phenomenon.%20The%20composition%20of%20the%20bench%20was%20cisgendered-heterosexual%20savarna%20judges%20%E2%80%93%20four%20men%20and%20one%20woman%20(who%20did%20not%20give%20her%20judgment).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERepresentation%20and%20diversity%20are%20critical%20for%20juridical%20review%20and%20action%20in%20locating%20agency%20and%20voice%20for%20a%20community%20that%20is%20otherwise%20marginalised%20%E2%80%93%20and%20discriminated%20against%20based%20on%20their%20identity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20collegium%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FCollegium%2F19012023_105547.pdf%5C%22%3Ereaffirmed%20the%20recommendation%20for%20appointing%20advocate%20Saurabh%20Kirpal%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20Delhi%20high%20court%20judge%2C%20dismissing%20the%20law%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20about%20his%20sexual%20orientation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsaurabh-kirpal-appointment-supreme-court-collegium-reiterate%5C%22%3EAlthough%20it%20has%20long%20been%20speculated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20advocate%E2%80%99s%20homosexuality%20brought%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20opposition%2C%20the%20collegium%20has%20now%20officially%20verified%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20addition%2C%20in%20his%20judgment%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20directed%20the%20government%20to%20form%20a%20committee%20to%20determine%20the%20rights%20and%20entitlements%20of%20those%20who%20are%20in%20queer%20partnerships%2C%20including%20ration%20cards%2C%20the%20ability%20for%20queer%20couples%20to%20nominate%20for%20joint%20bank%20accounts%2C%20rights%20resulting%20from%20pension%2C%20gratuity%2C%20etc.%20However%2C%20no%20direction%20has%20been%20issued%20towards%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20summation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EManan%20Kumar%20Mishra%2C%20an%20attorney%20and%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Bar%20Council%20of%20India%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scconline.com%2Fblog%2Fpost%2F2023%2F04%2F24%2Fmanan-kumar-mishra-advocate-and-chairman-bar-council-of-india-in-relation-to-same-sex-marriages-said-that-it-is-against-culture-and-civilization-of-india-legal-update-legal-research-legal-news%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAdvertisement-%2CIn%2520an%2520interview%252C%2520Mr.%2Csupports%2520these%2520types%2520of%2520marriages.%5C%22%3Ehas%20persistently%20fought%20against%20same-sex%20unions%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20claiming%20that%20they%20are%20incompatible%20with%20the%20ideals%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20culture%20and%20civilisation.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20no%20Indian%20faith%20endorses%20such%20couplings.%20These%20views%20were%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20supported%20by%20the%20verdict%20issued%20today%2C%20which%20emphasised%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%E2%80%99s%20guiding%20principles.%20These%20interpretations%20place%20limitations%20on%20people%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20abandon%20their%20queer%20or%20transgender%20identity%20to%20gain%20full%20recognition%20as%20citizens%20under%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnujslawreview.org%2F2020%2F08%2F31%2Funjust-citizenship-the-law-that-isnt%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20nation%20has%20a%20history%20of%20legislative%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20particularly%20evident%20in%20the%20language%20used%20and%20the%20misinterpretation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20self-determination%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20gender%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F13091%2F1%2Fa2019-40.pdf%5C%22%3ETransgender%20Persons%20Right%20to%20Protection%20Act%2C%202019%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Delegating%20the%20responsibility%20of%20marriage%20equality%20to%20the%20legislature%20would%20be%20no%20less%20of%20a%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETavleen%20Kaur%3Cspan%3E%20is%20senior%20research%20assistant%20and%20team%20lead%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESwabhimaan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20initiative%20with%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20She%20is%20studying%20Law%20at%20the%20Jindal%20Global%20Law%20School.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3Cspan%3E%20is%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20CNES%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20Anvitha%20V.%20Gowda%20is%20a%20research%20assistant%20with%20CNES%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Swabhimaan%20initiative.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20read%20more%20of%20Team%20Swabhimaan%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20please%20access%20its%20website%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswabhimaannetin.files.wordpress.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697636728000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18190519%2FDelhi-Pride-Parade-LGBTQ-rights-13.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftwo-steps-forward-three-steps-back-supreme-court-verdict-marriage-equality%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Social%20battles%20for%20securing%20and%20exercising%20legal%20rights%20are%20affected%20by%20factors%20such%20as%20power%2C%20unequal%20access%20to%20res